eventText: Deepak made the changes in the DD and sent it back to Dominik for approval.
Sambhaji sent the app store, Amazon, GA requirements to Dominik.
ACR sent a lots of feedback on the design draft.
Mariona asks Deepak, if Deepak will take care of the changes. Shantanu replied that he has already transferred the changes to Deepak.
Deepak says, he will implement the changes and will send the PDF. Mariona is fine with it.
Dominik says, we will use our own AWS S3 bucket.
Deepak completes the changes and resend the DD for approvals.
Dominik informs that the DD is with client now for approvals.
Shantanu sends the ACR app TOC, data for approvals to Dominik.
Dominik asks Shantanu to update the ACR timeline in Redmine.
Shantanu requests Dominik to provide excel sheets for 3 tools, FRAX score, FORE score, QFracture score
Treatment of Rheumatoid Arthritis guideline is on CMS, @9Mar
Glucocorticoid Induced Osteoporosis guideline is on CMS, 12Mar
The changes for DD arrived from client, forwarded by Dominik.
DD is sent to client for approval.
Perioperative Management of Antirheumatic Medication guideline is on CMS, @14Mar.
Shantanu informs Dominik that ACR 3 guidelines are available on CMS.
ACR app design draft is finalised by client.
Android Google Play developer invitation received and accepted.
Sambhaji sends reminder email to Dominik for iTunes and Google play developer console.
iTunes connect invitation received and accepted. Android account is also accessible.
Dominik has asked to remove QFracture tool from the ACR app.

Dominik has asked to add 5 criteria guidelines as content and not as links. Also, 2010 Rheumatoid Arthritis Classification Criteria we will delete the algo tool (because the score in the GL is better)
